<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Monmouth" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Monmouth,</orth> birthplace of Henry V, who therefore bore the name of Henry M. before his accession: <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.2.50" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 2, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.4.59" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 59</bibl>. H4B Ind. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.4.59" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 59</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.1.19" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 1, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.3.45" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.7.12" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 7, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.7.12" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 7, 12</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.7.12" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 7, 12</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.7.12" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 7, 12</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.7.12" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 7, 12</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.5.23" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 5, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.1.198" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 198</bibl>. <cit><quote>M. caps:</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.7.104" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 7, 104</bibl></cit> (the place being formerly famous for the caps made there).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>